reviews.text:
I would recommend a visit to Seascale and the West Cumbria coastal path which runs from Seascale up to the Sellafield nuclear plant. 
The views of the sea are most stunning especially on a sunny day. 
The views of the sunlight reflecting off the sea water is most stunning. 
I would recommend a visit to Seascale in Cumbria.
If you want somewhere to stay I would strongly recommend the Calder House Hotel in Seascale.  It is right on coastline of West Cumbria.
